Từ điển Anh - Việt
◘['sentə]
*danh từ & động từ
 ■(từ Mỹ,nghĩa Mỹ) (như) centre

Kết hợp từ & Cấu trúc câu
centerI
n.
point equally distant from all points on a circumference
1) dead center
2) at, in the center (at the center of a circle)
central point
3) a storm center (also fig.)
4) at, in a center (at the center of operations; right in the center of activity)
location where an activity takes place; focus of activity
5) an amusement; birthing (AE), childbearing (AE); business, commercial; civic; communications; community; convention; crisis; cultural; day-care; fashion; financial; health; industrial; job (BE); literary; manufacturing; medical; research; science; senior-citizen; separation (mil.); service; shopping; social; trade; wine-producing center
6) (fig.) a nerve; storm center
7) a national; world center
group of nerve cells
8) a nerve center
II
v. (d; intr., tr.) to center on, upon (attention centered on their opening statements)
